# Privacy Policy for Fondly

**Last updated: January 16, 2025**

## Data Collection

Fondly does not collect, store, or share any of your personal data.

## Data Storage

All data (contacts, thoughts, and interactions) is stored locally on your device. We do not have access to your data and it never leaves your device.

## Contacts Permission

Fondly requests access to your contacts only when you choose to import a contact during onboarding. This permission is optional and can be denied without affecting app functionality.

We do not:
- Upload your contacts to any server
- Share your contacts with third parties
- Store your contacts outside your device

## No Tracking

Fondly does not use:
- Analytics services
- Advertising networks
- Tracking technologies
- Third-party data collection tools

## Your Rights

You have complete control over your data:
- All data stays on your device
- You can delete your data at any time by deleting the app
- No account or registration required

## Children's Privacy

Fondly does not knowingly collect data from anyone, including children under 13.

## Changes to This Policy

If we update this privacy policy, we will notify you through the app or by updating this page.

## Contact

If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at:
fondly@mailbox.org

